default past underi
defaultnvestment, as well as 
defaultpreparing for
default large increases in
default required
default capacity, and researching and implementing solutions for 
defaultareas with enduring traffic issues.
default If properly implemented, this programme may alleviate the congestion that is estimated to cost the British economy up to £14bn per annum by 2025.
defaultMany opportunities are presented for efficiencies and smarter road usage.
default The government recognises the impo
defaultrtance of local road networks in supporting the strategic network, and is providing 
default£6 billion for their maintenance over the next six years. Building on this, we suggest that
default 
defaultr
defaultedefining the strategic road network to include key entry points and junctions 
defaultwould help avoid congestion at intersections between the SRN and the local system.
defaultThe programme also offers £500 million in support of low-carbon technologies, with the aim of reducing the environmental footprint of road travel. Economies of scale in larg
defaulte highway projects offer more opportunities to invest in environmental mitigation.  The potential spread of the managed motorways programme could deliver both cost and environmental efficiencies; the effects of this and other technological innovations are 
defaultdiscussed in section 4.
default 
defaultIn accordance with the recommendations of the Cook Report, independence from central government will 
defaultallo
defaultw the Highways Agency to realise large improvements for the strategic road network, 
defaultwhich will be discussed in 
defaultgreater
default detail below.
default The introduction of 5-year control periods will also allow for 
defaulta much longer planning horizon by freeing the Agency from the uncertainty of the annual Budget cycle. Furthermore, regulatory pressure is expected to create efficiencies of up to
default 20%
default in
default unit costs within 5 years of implementation, translating to £600 million in savings by 2020.
default Building on these plans, new funding options will also be available to the Agency.
