default3.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn recent years, travel by car has dropped somewhat in Britain, using kilometres travelled per person as a metr
defaultic. 
defaultThe Department for Transport’s forecasts acknowledge this decline, but do not appear to account for the reasons for it.
defaultStudies show that the
default 
defaultdecline is 
defaultlargely due to external factors, such as rising fuel prices, the cost of insurance and 
defaulttaxation.
default Should this trend continue, 
defaultprivate car 
defaultdemand may be lower in the coming years than currently predicted by the 
defaultgovernment.
default 
default 
defaultOn the other hand, r
defaultoad freight is also sharply increasing; in conjunction with the fall in car travel, this trend may be 
defaultconnected with the steady rise 
defaultin internet shopping
default. Thus
default, the fall in individual demand may be counterbalanced by the rise in commercial transport.
default As above, integrated planning is essential to deliver the capacity for increased freight traffic.
defaultThe gover
defaultnment can deal with uncertainty in 
defaultdemand 
defaultforecasts through the use of a range of 
defaultdifferent 
defaultforecasts
default rather than a monolithic one
default, and 
defaultalso by understanding how forecasts have been produced by 
defaultbreaking down predictions into 
defaulttheir 
defaultconstituent parts. For example, an exogenous growth forecast could be based upon 
defaultchanges in factors such as 
defaultGDP
default (for disposable income)
default, population growth, employment, fuel costs and insurance costs
default. 
defaultBy understanding the assumptions behind and the signific
defaultance of each of these factors, forecasts can be updated as economic indicators 
defaultchange over time.  
defaultThe Department for Transport currently utilises a 
defaultregularly updated Rail Usage Demand Database from which 
defaultforecasts of 
defaultrail 
defaultpassenger demand
default are derived
default.
default A si
defaultmilar system could be established for roads.
default4.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe r
defaulteliability 
defaultand efficiency of travel 
defaulton the strategic road network can be improved through 
defaultthe implementation of 
defaultsmarter technology. 
defaultFor example t
defaulthe provision of real-time information to users 
defaultand the 
