default lead to tangible improvements in journey times. The Highways Agency is seeking to launch a workable driver information service through 
defaultsmartphones
default and GPS in 2014.
defaultThe use of laser scanners by police to record n
defaultecessary information from traffic incidents provides an average reduction of 40 minutes in road closures. 
defaultThis technology is currently being used by 
default27 police forces, and further investment should prove beneficial. By the same token, investment in safety m
defaulteasures prevents incidents and further improves the reliability of the network. 
defaultThe results of the M42 managed motorway trial suggest that widespread implementation of this programme 
defaultc
defaultould sharply reduce the incidence of accidents and fatalities, increase 
defaultcapacity a
defaultnd decrease journey times. Additionally, emissions and noise levels are also reduced.
defaultOne aim of t
defaulthe government’s current investment programme
default is to resurface 80% of the strategic road network by 2021, as well as carrying out other maintenance and enhancement projects.
default Res
defaulturfacing
default 
defaultreduces the amount of damage caused 
defaultto vehicles from potholes, decreasing the number of breakdowns and improving
default eff
defaulticiency
default. 
defaultHowever, the challenge of managing road space and maintaining journey time reliability during such a significant programme of investment must be addressed; as most work is already carried out at night, options for avoiding disruption are limited.
defaultRevising the Agency’s funding cycle to a 5-year regulatory period would facilitate a constant stream of maintenance work, as opposed to the discontinuous nature of the annual budgetary cycle. 
defaultThis transition also presents the opportunity to redefine the st
defaultrategic road network to include key entry points and junctions, helping to avoid congestion at intersections between the SRN and local system
defaults
default.
defaultOther new technology can address environmental concerns while delivering efficiencies and reliability; 
defaultcurrently, a system of ‘smart’ highways is being piloted in the Netherlands, which includes solar-powered street markings to indicate wet or icy sections of road, and windmill-powered efficient street lighting that is only active when vehicles are within a
default certain range, saving large amo
defaultunts i
defaultn energy costs. This project should be closely observed, and if successful and cost-effective, implemented in the UK.
defaultAs detailed below, converting the strategic road network into a regulated utility will create a clea
defaultr, long-term output specification for performance with well-defined standards for safety and resilience, and the Highways Agency will be held to account for failures.
