default5.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe implementation of a Regulatory Asset Base (R
defaultAB) model is one option for increasing i
defaultnvestment in the strategic road network,
default and has been used extensively in the corporatisation of other public ass
defaultets in the UK
default and across Europe
default. Rail is the most similar sector, but it also applies to water, power and airports in the UK. 
defaultThis mo
defaultdel uses 
defaultthe valuation of network assets as a basis for setting access charges, outputs and incentive structures across predetermined control periods.
default Using such a structure would provide certainty of funding for the network, reducing the costs of uncertainty from 
defaultthe annual budgetary cycle. Instead, longer regulatory cycles would be used, providing investment horizons of 5 years or longer.
defaultT
defaulthe 
defaultstrategic road network
default would form the core 
defaultof a highways
default 
defaultRAB
default. The model has several advantages over a PPP or PFI model; 
defaultnamely that its cost of capital is cheaper, the valuation of its assets forms a solid and consistent foundation for a sustainable price control, and a pricing cap imposed by an independent regulator provides transparency and reassurance to consumers and fi
defaultnance providers. However, an accurate valuation of the entire SRN is likely to require a lengthy audit. Thus, an approximation will be necessary, with initial financing based on this valuation.
default Such an approximation
default was used
default in establishing the RAB for Net
defaultwork Rail.
default As a case s
defaulttudy, 
defaultthe use of the model in restructuring Scottish Water serve
defaults
default as an example of best practice
default, with drastic increases in quality of service concurrent with a 35% decrease in operational expenditures over a 10-year period
default.
defaultAs a 
defaultgovernment-owned company, the Highways Agency will be capable of borrowing from the private sector, allowing for increased financial flexibility.
default 
defaultThis is a
default 
defaultfeature of most regulatory regimes and 
defaultallows the company
default to manage
default 
defaultits business 
defaulteffectively over 
defaultre
defaultgulatory period
defaults. 
defaultSuch a reserve could also protect the
default 
defaultconsumer by 
defaultproviding insulation
default between long-term planning requirements and the shorter
default 
defaultterm public expenditure framework
default.
defaultThe precise method of securing a revenue 
defaultstream,
default and associated financing fo
defaultr the SRN cannot be finalised until broader policy questions on road charging have been considered. We are experienced in various approaches to tolling that are used to charge road users for access to strategic highways assets: for example, the Agency may 
defaultwish to adopt systems tailored by factors such as peak time, location and vehicle emissions. The European Union mandates that electronic toll systems be compatible with those on the continent, so it may be sensible to use a ‘badge’ system such as that used
default by the French, which seamlessly integrates toll systems from all regions with no work required on the part of the road user.
defaultIf an alternative method of charging is implemented, a transition
defaultal
default period of shadow tolling 
defaultis likely to be essential
default, in which
default the government
default 
defaultpay
defaults operators for road
default usage rather than 
defaultconsumers
default. 
